Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function, and low total CO₂, indicating possible metabolic acidosis. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), which may indicate renal tubular dysfunction or possible urinary tract pathology. HbA1c is low, not consistent with diabetes. Recommend further evaluation of renal function and possible nephrology referral.
